<td style=" color:#000000; font-size:12pt; background-color:#FFFFFF; font-family:arial; bLabel:main; bEditID:r3st1;" tEditID="c1r1" locked="0" aEditID="c1r1" >
<![CDATA[<div><font face="arial">Hi&nbsp;{!Lead.FirstName},</font></div><div><font face="arial"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial">Welcome to MBO Partners! I have just activated your account, so you’re ready to get started on your Bonneville Power Administration assignment.&nbsp;</font></div><div><font face="arial"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial">Below is some important information you should know about working with BPA. Please keep this email handy so that you can refer back to it as needed.</font></div><div><font face="arial"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial"><b>Entering Your Time and BPA-Billable Expenses</b></font></div><div><font face="arial">As you work, you are responsible for time, milestone, and expense entry (<a href="http://info.mbopartners.com/rs/mbo/images/BPA_SLIM_Time_Instructions.pdf">instructions</a>) in accordance with your Statement of Work with BPA. <u><b>Be sure to submit your entries by Sunday for the previous week’s work</b></u>.&nbsp;</font></div><div><font face="arial"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial">If you incur expenses that can be billed back to BPA, submit them through your MBO Business Center as well (<a href="http://info.mbopartners.com/rs/mbo/images/MBO_Exec_Time_and_Expense_Entry_Instructions.pdf">instructions</a>, pages 2 and 3).&nbsp;</font></div><div><font face="arial"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial"><b>Program Fee&nbsp;</b></font></div><div><font face="arial">There is a program fee associated with your BPA engagement. For qualified subcontractors, MBO collects a program fee (3.15% of your billings) as you work.</font></div><div><font face="arial"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial"><b>Payment Process and Timing</b></font></div><div><font face="arial">As we discussed during our consultation call, BPA pays MBO within 10 days of invoicing (which occurs bi-weekly). Based on these terms, and accommodating for payment processing, you will receive your funds approximately 20 days after invoicing. (Assumes BPA pays MBO within its payment terms.) Remember, failure to submit time by the deadline above will result in payment delays.</font></div><div><font face="arial"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 0);"><b>Ongoing Support</b></font></div><div><font face="arial" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 0);">I will be your primary support contact during your BPA engagement. If you have any questions or concerns, I’m here to help. Remember, MBO provides unlimited phone and email support while you work on your client assignments.&nbsp;</font><font face="arial" style="background-color: rgb(51, 204, 0);">If you are NOT transferring the Associate to a Business Manager, use this section and delete the one below.</font></div><div><font face="arial" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 0);"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 0);"><b>Ongoing Support</b></font></div><div><font face="arial" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 0);">Now that you’re enrolled, I am pleased to introduce you to your new point of contact, BM_Fullname. BM_Firstname will be taking on the long-term care of your account as your dedicated Business Manager. While you’re enrolled with MBO, BM_Firstname will serve as your advocate and support representative for day-to-day issues regarding payments, invoices, expenses, setting up new client contracts, and more. We have already reviewed your account history together and BM_Firstname looks forward to working with you. Of course, I am always here to help as well.</font></div><div><font face="arial" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 0);"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 0);">BM_Firstname will reach out to you soon to say hello and walk you through the MBO Business Center – your online window into all your financial activity. Or you can reach out directly at:</font></div><div><font face="arial" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 0);"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 0);">Telephone: (703) 793-XXXX</font></div><div><font face="arial" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 0);">Email: <a href="mailto:xxxxx@mbopartners.com">xxxxx@mbopartners.com</a>&nbsp;</font><font face="arial" style="background-color: rgb(51, 204, 0);">If you ARE immediately transferring the Associate to a Business Manager, use this section and delete the one above.</font></div><div><font face="arial">&nbsp;</font></div><div><font face="arial">Again, welcome to MBO! It has been a pleasure working with you and I appreciate your patience during the on-boarding process. On behalf of everyone here, I sincerely hope that we offer a positive experience as you pursue your independent goals.</font></div><div><font face="arial"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial">Best regards,</font></div><div><font face="arial"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial">{!Lead.Enrollment_Manager__c}</font></div><div><font face="arial">BPA Enrollment Manager</font></div><div><font face="arial">{!Lead.fs_emPhone__c}</font></div><div><font face="arial">{!Lead.EM_Email__c}</font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;"><br></div>]]></td>
